fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes

Interface ITemplatePackage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<ITemplatePackage>, IPackage, Iterable<ITemplateFile>

    public interface ITemplatePackage
extends IPackage, Comparable<ITemplatePackage>, Iterable<ITemplateFile>
    Represents a package of templates for a specific type of template system.

    Template packages can be used directly in for-each constructs, to iterate over template files.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent read/write access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • addStylePackage

        void addStylePackage(String packageName,
                     InputStream stream)
              throws IOException
        Uploads a style package in a recognized format for this template package using the supplied input stream. The template package must be modifiable; if not, this method will throw an exception.
        Parameters:
        packageName - identifies the package.
        stream - source for reading the package. Will be closed when the end is reached.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the package cannot be read or is invalid.
        UnsupportedThemeOperationException - if the package cannot be added due to the template package being unmodifiable, or if the operation fails due to the bundle providing the service being stopped.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IPackage.exportPackage(java.io.OutputStream)

      • removeStylePackage

        void removeStylePackage(String packageName)
                 throws IOException
        Removes a style package from this template package, deleting any associated files. The template package must be modifiable; if not, this method will throw an exception.
        Parameters:
        packageName - identifies the package.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the package cannot be removed.
        UnsupportedThemeOperationException - if the package cannot be removed due to the template package being unmodifiable, or if the operation fails due to the bundle providing the service being stopped.
        Since:
        1.0
